# Tejas Labs site environment

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values for local dev. In
production (Vercel), set the same variables in the project's Environment
Variables settings.

## Site

`NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`
  Public origin used in canonical URLs, Open Graph tags, sitemap, and robots.
  Example: `https://tejaslabs.co.in`

## Contact form (POST /api/contact)

The contact form on the site emails a brief to the studio Gmail. It uses
Gmail SMTP via Nodemailer, which requires a Google **app password** (not the
account password).

1. Enable 2-Step Verification on the Gmail account.
2. Visit https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords and create an app password
   for "Mail" / "Other (Tejas Labs site)".
3. Put the 16-character password below.

`GMAIL_USER`
  The Gmail address that sends the email.
  Example: `tejaslabs0028@gmail.com`

`GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD`
  The 16-character Gmail app password from step 2 above. No spaces.

`CONTACT_TO` (optional)
  Where the brief is delivered. Defaults to the value of `GMAIL_USER`.
  Useful if you want submissions to land in a different inbox.

## Chatbot (POST /api/chat)

The floating site receptionist calls OpenCode Go from a server-only route.
Never expose this key as a `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variable.

`OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY`
  OpenCode Go API key used by the chatbot route.

`OPENCODE_GO_BASE_URL` (optional)
  OpenAI-compatible base URL. Defaults to `https://opencode.ai/zen/v1`.

`OPENCODE_GO_MODEL` (optional)
  Chat model. Defaults to `nemotron-3-ultra-free`.
